The paper deals with image segmentation and object recognition in microscopy images, which is a common problem in computer vision (cs.CV). The authors also use deep learning techniques to achieve state-of-the-art results, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper involves the use of synthetic images for training, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The authors also mention the potential use of their methodology in different applications, which could fall under information retrieval (cs.IR) or multimedia (cs.MM).
